\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
 High efforts are chosen as long as 
\begin_inset Formula $pU(X)+(1-p)U(Y)-C\ge qU(X)+(1-q)U(Y)\Rightarrow(p-q)(U(X)-U(Y))\Rightarrow C$
\end_inset

.
 Under the second best scheme, individual consumption must move with individual
 income.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size footnotesize
Considering, the reliability of a mutual insurance scheme, let us consider
 the gain from a high output individual who breaks the contract 
\begin_inset Formula $G=U(H)-U(M)$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $M=pH+(1-p)L).$
\end_inset

